{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"730a33e0-73f3-420f-ad65-5fe06718539f","content":"The directory is empty — there's no existing project yet. No worries, here's exactly what you need to configure to publish a C# MCP server as a **dotnet tool** on NuGet.org:\n\n### Key `.csproj` properties\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n\n    <!-- These make it a dotnet tool -->\n    <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n    <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n    <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n    <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n    <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n    <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n    <Description>An MCP server over stdio.</Description>\n    <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n    <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/you/MyMcpServer</PackageProjectUrl>\n    <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/you/MyMcpServer</RepositoryUrl>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n### Publish steps\n\n```bash\n# 1. Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# 2. Push (get your API key from https://www.nuget.org/account/apikeys)\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install & run with\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server   # launches stdio MCP server\n```\n\n### Essential points\n\n- **`PackAsTool`** — the critical property that makes `dotnet pack` produce a tool package.\n- **`ToolCommandName`** — the CLI command name users will type (defaults to the assembly name if omitted).\n- **`OutputType` must be `Exe`** — tools must be console apps.\n- Your `Main` / top-level code should read from stdin and write to stdout for the stdio MCP transport.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d4ec436c-fbdc-4d5b-bcd3-0e2e4db9e467","outputTokens":554},"id":"17df16e5-8f2f-46b1-b915-e3c84afbd7e8","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:54:04.382Z","parentId":"10f01e9e-93e0-4a89-96a4-d88aa65b9f15"}
